method.name: Axis Parallel Rectangle (APR) algorithm

reference.ref: T. G. Dietterich, R. H. Lathrop, T. Lozano-Perez. Solving the Multiple-Instance Problem with Axis-Parallel Rectangles. Artificial Intelligence Journal, 89, 1997.

generalDescription.objective: To determine a classification model for multiple instance learning based on APR algorithm.
generalDescription.howWork: Dietterich et al. (1997) proposed a series of MIL algorithms formulated as finding an axis-parallel rectangle (APR) in the feature space as the target concept. APR_IteratedDiscrimination is an iterative, discriminative variant which is empirically proved to outperforms all other variants.

parameterSpec.param: alpha: It is the value that is received by an instance is the only remaining instance of a bag.
epsilon: It specifies the amount of probability that should lie outside the expanded bounds of the APR along each feature dimension.
tau: It determines the width of the gaussian kernel
